The PERFECT post-thanksgiving recipe (with four suggested substitutes): switch out the chicken for turkey, -use turkey stock from boiling the carcass, leftover seasonings, drippings, etc., -possible alternative to pie crust is to pile on mashed potatoes (shephard's pie, essentially) - vegetable options: peas, broccoli, and potato instead of turnips. This year, we had leftover bacon/brussel sprouts to add to the mix. One other note: for kid friendly cooking, have individual 4-5" ramekins, having prepared ingredients separately, display them in an assembly line, and let kids/guests choose their favorite vegetable options to mix in with rest of ingredients. Then let them finish off with their own pastry decoration/potato sculpture.

