Rating: 4
I've made this repeatedly, and it's always an enormous hit. I substitute a bag of organic baby spinach for the turnip greens, and use a few small turnips as well as a few parsnips for some sweetness. No potatoes, as they would absorb sauce, making the pot pie too dry. One thing I've found makes a wonderful addition is a small amount of sliced jarred pimento, well drained (I dry it completely on paper towels). It adds some sparkle to an otherwise pale-looking dish and a subtle, bright flavor. The crust is easy to make if you use cold ingredients and mix it in a food processor up to the stage where you mix in water with a fork. (You can now get transfat-free shortening, which is a plus and yields the same good results.)

