I needed some serious comfort food the day after a plumbing disaster, and this was exactly what I was craving. A hug with a flaky golden crust. Of course, I tweaked it depending on what I had on hand: spinach (not greens), dried thyme, butter not shortening, and I substituted about a quarter cup of corn meal for some of the flour to give the crust more texture. I used low fat half & half instead of cream, and spring onions instead of leeks, and the sauce was still so good we actually ate the little bit left over with a spoon while the pie baked (embarassing, but true). One bit of advice: use a decent (not cooking) wine. (Luna di Luna was great--have a glass while you're chopping everything up.) It was long process, but not hard, and very worth it. I can't wait to get home to a dry house and leftovers!

