Delicious. My kids, ages 6 and 9, love this dish. My husband says it is the BEST POT PIE he's ever tasted. I have made it twice now -- once as a pot pie using a Pilsbury pie crust and once as a shepherd's pie using mashed potatoes as a crust. (The kids liked this the best). I used chicken and pork loin chops (cubed) for the meat. For the vegetables, I add whatever I have in the house that strikes my fancy -- carrots, russet potatoes, sweet potatoes, red lentils, frozen green beans, green peas, spinach, leeks, onions, red and orange bell peppers, zucchini, summer squash, portabella mushrooms. Next time, for convenience, I will substitute a reduced calorie cream of chicken soup for the sauce. Since I add so many vegetables, I end up with enough filling for three or four pies. I freeze the additional filling in ziploc freezer bags. Then, when I want a quick meal, I can defrost it, top it with a pie crust or mashed potatoes, and --VOILA -- a gourmet meal in less than an hour! This has become a regular feature in our family's meal plans.

