Rating: 4
This pot-pie had the whole family drooling! It was wonderful and I thank previous reviewers for tips on adding other veggies. I do not like turnips, so substituted potatoes, substituted baby spinach and added celery and mushrooms. The herb crust really makes the dish. One note -- double or triple wash the spinach! I made the crust on Friday, the filling on Saturday and then put the two together on Sunday and this was a fabulous Sunday Birthday dinner for Dad.

Rating: 4
This is one of my most favorite things to make in the fall. The preparation is a bit consuming, but the dish is just so wonderful. I have fed many large groups on this pie. I love the crust so much that one time I tried to double it. Bad idea, made the crust too heavey instead of light and wonderful. Outstanding!

Rating: 4
This is one of the few 4-fork ratings I have awarded a recipe. I made this when the the fall issue first came out in 1999 and have made it at least 7 times since. It is absolutely delish and looks spectacular. I do the leaf cut outs and brush the entire top with an egg wash. People just love this...true comfort food. I also add a stick or two of carrots and a large celery stalk. I also use spinach instead of turnip greens as it is easier. I used greens the first time and couldn't taste them. Plus the spinach retains a nicer color. I also use a small turnip and a large potato. The last time I added a bunch of fresh green beans (cut into 1/2 pieces) that I had lying around. Make this -- you'll love it. The crust is wonderful. I wouldn't use a store bought. Take the time...have a glass of wine and cook away! Bon Appetite!

