Rating: 2
I am quite positive that this recipe yields a four fork rating if prepared properly. However, unfortunately, I took the liberty of adding extra liquid to the pot pie. This was a huge mistake because the beautifully speckled herb crust sunk like the Titanic into the depths of the pot pie. I attempted a rescue mission by pouring out some of the pot pie's liquid midway through its cooking time. Regrettably, I lost the delicious cream sauce. I will definitely try this recipe again, but, I will follow the directions. Some changes that I made were to add some new potatoes to the turnips and peas instead of turnip greens. The color of the peas became bland so I would not use them again. Also, I used chives and thyme for the herbs. My boyfriend liked the pot pie but did not love it.

