Rating: 3
Absolutely wonderful -- I've made a lot of pot pies and this is the best yet. Because my kids won't eat anything with green specks I skipped the thyme and it still had lots of rich flavor. Additionally, I substituted light cream for whipping -- didn't miss the extra fat one bit. I also topped the dish with puff pastry as a shortcut and thought it was fine, but it didn't add much. If I don't have time to make the herb crust next time, I'll just serve the chicken mixture over slices of French bread and skip the pastry altogether.

