Rating: 4
A VERY tasty sauce--I recommend the recipe, with a few substitutions; I used carrots (3), celery (3 stalks), mushrooms (8 oz.), and onion (1/2) for my filling. My sauce needed a bit more wine. The crust however was too 'short' in my opinion, disolving in the mouth (too much shortening)--and it turned green due to the parsley. Next time I will use a traditional pie dough recipe, with the addition of 2 Tbsp chopped fresh thyme. It is a time-consuming endeavor, but worth it, especially if you double the recipe so you can freeze one pie for another time!

